  "prompt": "Can you make Bisquick pancakes without eggs?",
  "response": "Yes, you can make Bisquick pancakes without eggs by using egg substitutes. Here are a few options:\n\n1. Mashed banana:\n- 1/4 cup mashed banana per egg\n- Adds moisture and binding properties\n\n2. Applesauce:\n- 1/4 cup unsweetened applesauce per egg\n- Provides moisture and helps bind ingredients\n\n3. Ground flaxseed or chia seed mixture:\n- 1 tablespoon ground flaxseed or chia seeds + 3 tablespoons water per egg\n- Let sit for a few minutes to thicken\n- Acts as a binding agent\n\n4. Commercial egg replacer:\n- Follow package instructions\n- Available in many grocery stores\n\n5. Yogurt or buttermilk:\n- 1/4 cup per egg\n- Adds moisture and helps with texture\n\nWhen substituting eggs, you may need to adjust the liquid-to-dry ingredient ratio slightly to achieve the right pancake consistency. Start with the recommended substitute and add more liquid if the batter seems too thick.\n\nTips:\n- Whisk the egg substitute well before adding to the Bisquick mix\n- Let the batter rest for a few minutes before cooking",
